On Monday, June 18, 2007, at 04:00PM, "Mike Soultanian" <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

>I think I have the same relay kit.  Does it reach the starter terminals 
>ok?

I bought my Bosch WR-1 kit from Bus Depot. The wires were long enough and not tight. The only hard part was fitting the spade terminals through the grommet (not that hard really).

>There's a wire on the double-relay that goes to the starter. If you  
>put the starter button over there then there's nothing to worry about  
>during an engine drop.
>
>Bonus: The double-relay is much easier to access than the regulator  
>if the bus is loaded full of camping gear....

True but you often want a remote starter that doesn't cause fuel to be sprayed so it's a little extra effort to configure it for both cases.

